{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Another Chris","author":"Chris Small"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"94ba69be-801d-543b-a18d-8b6b2e4fe62a","excerpt":"If you have to insert XML into a SQL Server (2005+) XML column, there’s three ways of doing it. Perform a raw string insert, which is unlikely to work Use an…","html":"<p>If you have to insert XML into a SQL Server (2005+) XML column, there’s three ways of doing it.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Perform a raw string insert, which is unlikely to work</li>\n<li>Use an XmlReader and SqlDbType.Xml</li>\n<li>Use SqlDbType.Text and a Stream.</li>\n</ol>\n<!--more-->\n<p>Below is my preferred way of doing it and gets around the problem you might come up with:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>XML parsing: line 1, character (xx),<br>\nunable to switch the encoding </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This occurs when you’re trying to shove a UTF8 string into the database XML column, using</p>\n<pre>&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?&gt;</pre>\n<p>It might also happen with a file with no BOM, which can be fixed by opening + saving the file in notepad. Anyway the solution below gets around this issue.</p>\n<p><div id=\"gist4984662\" class=\"gist\">\n    <div class=\"gist-file\">\n      <div class=\"gist-data\">\n        <div class=\"js-gist-file-update-container js-task-list-container file-box\">\n  <div id=\"file-gistfile1-cs\" class=\"file\">\n    \n\n  <div itemprop=\"text\" class=\"Box-body p-0 blob-wrapper data type-c \">\n      \n<table class=\"highlight tab-size js-file-line-container\" data-tab-size=\"8\">\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-gistfile1-cs-L1\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"1\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-gistfile1-cs-LC1\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">using</span> <span class=\"pl-en\">System</span>.<span class=\"pl-en\">IO</span>;</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-gistfile1-cs-L2\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"2\"></td>\n  